article.headline: Western Kentucky 80, Louisiana-Lafayette 72
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Winchester had 33 points to lead Western Kentucky into the Sun Belt tournament final with an 80-72 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Monday night. Western Kentucky (23-6) will seek its sixth tournament title against South Alabama on Tuesday night. The Jaguars advanced with a 75-65 win over Denver earlier in the evening. Winchester scored eight of his points, including six consecutive free throws, after Louisiana-Lafayette had trimmed the Hilltoppers lead to 70-66 with 2:07 left to play. He earlier hit a pair of 3-pointers to lead a 12-4 charge that broke a 41-41 deadlock midway through the second half. Winchester had seven straight points in just over one minute to propel the Hilltoppers to an 18-8 advantage early in the first half. Louisiana-Lafayette (13-16) fought back to pull even, 22-22, on a jumper by Dwayne Mitchell with 8:46 left in the half. Michael Southall had a pair of baskets as the Ragin' Cajuns went on another 12-1 run late for a 34-32 at the half. Southall hit 12-of-18 shots and finished with 30 points to pace the Ragin' Cajuns. Louisiana-Lafayette had won the tournament and the league's automatic berth in the NCAA Tournament the past two years.
